IN OUR WAITING, GOD IS WORKING

Yesaya 55:8 "Sebab rancangan-Ku bukanlah rancanganmu, dan jalanmu bukanlah jalan-Ku, demikianlah firman TUHAN."
.
Saat kita mau makan di restaurant mewah favorite, kita bisa rela dandan yg anggun cantik dan ganteng, rela nunggu sampai nama kita dipanggil dr waiting lists, & masih rela pesen walaupun tau tetap harus menunggu lagi. Pokoknya rela nunggu demi makanan itu. Saat menunggu kita sudah membayangkan rasanya makanan itu masuk mulut kita hmmyummy...tapi tetap excited kita menunggu hidangan yang kita idam-idamkan, walaupun kita tidak melihat, tidak tahu bagaimana makanan itu dimasak, tapi percaya aja sama chef di dapur, percaya pasti hidangannya enak dan pasti tiba di meja saat sudah matang.
.
Mungkin saat ini juga kita sedang menanti-nantikan jawaban doa kita. 
Mungkin dalam masa penantian kita, ada kalanya kita merasa Tuhan diam saja, Tuhan tidak mendengar doa kita, hingga kita mulai berhenti berdoa, berhenti mencari Tuhan. Mengapa? Karena kita salah fokus justru pada pergumulan kita, pada saat-saat menunggu yang membosankan. Kita tidak melihat sesuatu apapun terjadi sekarang, tapi percayalah Tuhan sedang bekerja di "dapurNya" dan pekerjaanNya tak terselami karena amat sangat jauuuh lebiiih indah dari semua yang kita bayangkan. Tuhan sedang mengerjakannya sesuai rancanganNya yang terbaik untuk diberikan pada kita pada waktu "matang" yang terbaik pula. 
Jika kita tetap percaya dan fokus pada Tuhan, pada janji dan kuasaNya, maka dalam masa penantian kita menanti dengan penuh sukacita seakan-akan kita tidak dalam masa penantian yang membosankan tp seperti kita sudah menerimanya, dan pasti-bukan niscaya-kita menerimanya. Tetaplah berdoa.
.
Kalau chef di restaurant bisa kita percaya memberikan hidangan terbaik, bukankah kita seharusnya bisa jauh lebih percaya pada Tuhan pencipta segala sesuatu? 
1 Tes 5:16-18 "Bersukacitalah senantiasa. Tetaplah berdoa. Mengucap syukurlah dalam segala hal, sebab itulah yang dikehendaki Allah di dalam Kristus Yesus bagi kamu."
#God1st #Godbless #bibleverse #godisworkingonyou

Jadilah seperti Ribka, ia dengan setia datang ke mata air untuk menimba air, berjalan kaki cukup jauh membawa buyung, menimba air, mengisi buyung, membawa buyung itu berjalan kaki kembali ke rumah. Ia tidak tau apa yang akan terjadi padanya di hari itu di saat ia datang ke mata air yang sama melakukan tugas yang sama, ia tidak tau ia akan bertemu dengan hamba Abraham, yang datang menjemputnya agar ia menjadi istri Ishak. Ia hanya setia pada tugasnya. Jika saat itu ia tidak datang ke mata air yang sama, tidak menimba air, dan tidak memberi minum pada orang yang asing baginya itu bahkan semua untanya, ia tidak akan mengalami mujizat. Tapi karena kesetiaannya pada tugasnya, karena ia terus datang ke mata air yang sama, ia mengalami mujizat yang telah ditetapkan Tuhan bagi dia untuk menjadi istri Ishak. (Kejadian 24:1-67)

caption.text:
ADJUST YOUR FOCUS
When life gets blurry adjust your focus.
.
.
.
Studying architecture has been really c-r-a-z-y, specially this 3rd semester. there are moments I can't really tell whether it is still today or it is the next day already. The time felt ticking uncontrollably fast. But there's one thing I realize through all these, though the journey is not easy and i might face (even more) difficult things, my God is always always and always with me. He gives me strength and keeps the joy in my heart in every step. In the midst of the crazy schedule of archi-life He reminds me to focus on Him and that He is possible God even when it seems impossible for me, to focus on His greatness not on my weaknesses. 
And He reminds me of the true calling of preparing something much much greater than just the tasks i'm doing in everyday everyweek of this semester or the upcoming semesters, that is His coming. 
#God1st #Godblessweekend #happyweekend #cantwaitforChristmas

BEYOND MEASURE 
Gen 41:49 NIV "Joseph collected all the food produced in those seven years of abundance in Egypt and stored it in the cities. In each city he put the food grown in the fields surrounding it. Joseph stored up huge quantities of grain, like the sand of the sea; it was so much that he stopped keeping records because it was beyond measure." Joseph was hated by his brothers so they sold him to the Midianites who sold him to Paraoh's officer. He went through many things in Egypt, but God never leaves him and made him prosper. 
In man's point of view, if we're Joseph we might think 'what a terrible life it is', we might even hate and blame our brothers (for the rest of our lives) for selling us and made us live far far away we have no idea about, where we know no one to ask for help. 
As human, we tend focus on the hardships, the problems, the terrible circumtances we are being put in. But look, if he has't gone through all these: if his brothers hasn't sell Joseph, he wouldn't reach Egypt, he wouldn't live in Paraoh's place, he wouldn't meet and interpret the cupbearer and the baker's dream, he wouldn't meet and interpret Paraoh's dream, he wouldn't be the ruler of all Egypt, and in the end he wouldn't be able to provides food and save Egyptians and all the world from great famine including his brothers and his beloved father! 
Joseph own a right heart and see things through God's point of view, so inspite of blaming his brothers, he said “And now, do not be distressed and do not be angry with yourselves for selling me here, because it was to save lives that God sent me ahead of you. For two years now there has been famine in the land, and for the next five years there will be no plowing and reaping. But God sent me ahead of you to preserve for you a remnant on earth and to save your lives by a great deliverance. “So then, it was not you who sent me here, but God. He made me father to Pharaoh, lord of his entire household and ruler of all Egypt.”
‭‭Gen45:5-8‬ ‭NIV‬‬
From a human's narrow measurements God turn it into something beyond measure. 
God has turn Joseph who bring nothing to Egypt, into Joseph who rules over something beyond measure.

• WE ARE LOVED •

We are loved before we even heard the word. 
John 3: 16 For God so loved the world that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him shall not perish but have eternal life.

Without His Love, there's no salvation and we are living in sin right now. 
Without His Love, we wouldn't even be here because there is no life but perish. 
But because He Loves us we are redeemed by His holy blood at the cross. So now we're alive and know the word 'love'. Cross equal love. 
1 John 4:19 We love because He first loved us. 
Love isn't about valentine's day we celebrated days ago.
Yes we do love someone, family, friends, everyone. 
And yes it's not wrong to express our love to them especially in valentine's day. 
But how do we express our love to Him who loves us eternally? 
Do you believe that you are Loved?

Loving others in the Love of Christ, the right way, not in the world's way, means we are doing His command. And so, expressing our love for Him. 
John 15:12 My command is this: Love each other as I have loved you. 
Because He loves me, I know how great it is to be loved, and able to love others. I always want to love Him more and more. I wish I could love like He has Loved me.
Thank You Jesus ❤️ #God1st #bibleverse #love #LoveofChrist #crossequallove #valentines2016

• Christmas Special Gift •

Keep Jesus Christ in your Christmas celebrations is to have him present in your daily life, not only on December 25th. Accept Jesus as your Savior and made him the center of your life. 
Keeping Christ in Christmas means daily revealing the character, love and spirit of Christ that dwells in you, by allowing these traits to shine through your actions to everyone.
Keeping Christ in Christmas is more about the way you live your life than the things you say, such as "Merry Christmas" or "Happy Holidays" etc. Keeping Christ in Christmas also means giving Him one very special gift. Let this gift be something personal that no one else needs to know about, and let it be a sacrifice. Perhaps your gift will be spending more time with God. Whatever it is, make it your most important gift of the season for God, a Christmas special gift to Jesus on His born day for you have received everything from Him.  Moreover, you may discover that you've given a gift back to yourself without waiting for the unreal Santa Claus;) #God1st #christmas2015 #december2015 #Jesus #Godblessweekend
